creator: Mogile Technologies
descriptionHtml:
ChargeHub's EV & Tesla Charging Stations Map App is every EV Driver's Best Friend!

EV ChargeHub (previously EV Charger Locator) is a must have App for all American & Canadian electric car owners who want to find EV charging stations locations to plug their Tesla Model S / Leaf / iMiEV / Volt / Focus EV / Plug-in Prius / Smart EV / BMW i3 / Kia Soul EV / etc.

Follow us on Twitter @EVChargeHub

-- What EV ChargeHub does --
EV & Tesla Charging Stations Map Interface:
-Find public electric vehicle charging stations
-Get driving directions to nearest EV or Tesla charging station
-Over 120 000 electric car charging station plugs (ev plugs) in the US & Canada
-See whats around while you recharge. Plugin your electric car & see what restaurants, hotels, parks, places are around your EV or Tesla charging station
-Get color coded live availability data from EV charging stations in the following networks: Chargepoint, Blink, Hydro Quebec's Circuit Electrique and AddEnergie Flo
-Found a new public charging station? Add it to the EV Charge Hub database
-Rate & add comments for all public electric vehicle supply equipment
-Use search feature to find Level 1, Level 2 (EV Plug) and DC Fast chargers (Tesla Superchargers, SAE DC Fast & CHAdeMO) anywhere across North America
-Smooth & responsive interface
-Filter and search EV charging stations to only display the ones you want (by network, by charging level, etc)
-Google Streetview to make it easier to see what's around an EV plug
-Directly call the network EVSE from the app to get more information (ex: Chargepoint, Tesla Supercharger, evGO, Blink, Electric Circuit, SemaCharge, VERnetwork)
-See traffic conditions directly on map & select map type
-Unique logos for Tesla Superchargers, SAE DC Fast chargers and CHAdeMO charging stations
-Share complete EV charging station info
-Detailed usage data for BC evCloud connected EV charging stations
-Request permission from other EV users for charger use ("plugshare-ing")
-In app charge session payment for selected networks

-- EV ChargeHub Features In Development --
-In app EV range estimation

Who should download EV Charge Hub:
-Electric car owners who want to find EV charging stations
-Prospective buyers of Tesla ModelS / Leaf / iMiEV / Volt / Focus EV / Plug-in Prius / Smart EV / Kia Soul EV / etc, who want to know where electric vehicle charging stations are before purchasing an electric car
descriptionShort: Join the community! Plan your trip & share comments and pics with other drivers

EV ChargeHub (previously EV Charger Locator) is a must have App for all American & Canadian electric car owners who want to find EV charging stations locations to plug their Tesla Model S / Leaf / iMiEV / Volt / Focus EV / Plug-in Prius / Smart EV / BMW i3 / Kia Soul EV / etc.

Follow us on Twitter @EVChargeHub

-- What EV ChargeHub does --
EV & Tesla Charging Stations Map Interface:
-Find public electric vehicle charging stations
-Get driving directions to nearest EV or Tesla charging station
-Over 120 000 electric car charging station plugs (ev plugs) in the US & Canada
-See whats around while you recharge. Plugin your electric car & see what restaurants, hotels, parks, places are around your EV or Tesla charging station
-Get color coded live availability data from EV charging stations in the following networks: Chargepoint, Blink, Hydro Quebec's Circuit Electrique and AddEnergie Flo
-Found a new public charging station? Add it to the EV Charge Hub database
-Rate & add comments for all public electric vehicle supply equipment
-Use search feature to find Level 1, Level 2 (EV Plug) and DC Fast chargers (Tesla Superchargers, SAE DC Fast & CHAdeMO) anywhere across North America
-Smooth & responsive interface
-Filter and search EV charging stations to only display the ones you want (by network, by charging level, etc)
-Google Streetview to make it easier to see what's around an EV plug
-Directly call the network EVSE from the app to get more information (ex: Chargepoint, Tesla Supercharger, evGO, Blink, Electric Circuit, SemaCharge, VERnetwork)
-See traffic conditions directly on map & select map type
-Unique logos for Tesla Superchargers, SAE DC Fast chargers and CHAdeMO charging stations
-Share complete EV charging station info
-Detailed usage data for BC evCloud connected EV charging stations
-Request permission from other EV users for charger use ("plugshare-ing")
-In app charge session payment for selected networks

-- EV ChargeHub Features In Development --
-In app EV range estimation

Who should download EV Charge Hub:
-Electric car owners who want to find EV charging stations
-Prospective buyers of Tesla ModelS / Leaf / iMiEV / Volt / Focus EV / Plug-in Prius / Smart EV / Kia Soul EV / etc, who want to know where electric vehicle charging stations are before purchasing an electric car

ChargeHub's EV & Tesla Charging Stations Map App is every EV Driver's Best Friend!

EV ChargeHub (previously EV Charger Locator) is a must have App for all American & Canadian electric car owners who want to find EV charging stations locations to plug their Tesla Model S / Leaf / iMiEV / Volt / Focus EV / Plug-in Prius / Smart EV / BMW i3 / Kia Soul EV / etc.

Follow us on Twitter @EVChargeHub

-- What EV ChargeHub does --
EV & Tesla Charging Stations Map Interface:
-Find public electric vehicle charging stations
-Get driving directions to nearest EV or Tesla charging station
-Over 120 000 electric car charging station plugs (ev plugs) in the US & Canada
-See whats around while you recharge. Plugin your electric car & see what restaurants, hotels, parks, places are around your EV or Tesla charging station
-Get color coded live availability data from EV charging stations in the following networks: Chargepoint, Blink, Hydro Quebec's Circuit Electrique and AddEnergie Flo
-Found a new public charging station? Add it to the EV Charge Hub database
-Rate & add comments for all public electric vehicle supply equipment
-Use search feature to find Level 1, Level 2 (EV Plug) and DC Fast chargers (Tesla Superchargers, SAE DC Fast & CHAdeMO) anywhere across North America
-Smooth & responsive interface
-Filter and search EV charging stations to only display the ones you want (by network, by charging level, etc)
-Google Streetview to make it easier to see what's around an EV plug
-Directly call the network EVSE from the app to get more information (ex: Chargepoint, Tesla Supercharger, evGO, Blink, Electric Circuit, SemaCharge, VERnetwork)
-See traffic conditions directly on map & select map type
-Unique logos for Tesla Superchargers, SAE DC Fast chargers and CHAdeMO charging stations
-Share complete EV charging station info
-Detailed usage data for BC evCloud connected EV charging stations
-Request permission from other EV users for charger use ("plugshare-ing")
-In app charge session payment for selected networks

-- EV ChargeHub Features In Development --
-In app EV range estimation

Who should download EV Charge Hub:
-Electric car owners who want to find EV charging stations
-Prospective buyers of Tesla ModelS / Leaf / iMiEV / Volt / Focus EV / Plug-in Prius / Smart EV / Kia Soul EV / etc, who want to know where electric vehicle charging stations are before purchasing an electric car
descriptionShort: Map of all EV Charging Stations for all EV and PHEV car models (including Tesla)

EV ChargeHub (previously EV Charger Locator) is a must have App for all electric car owners in the US and Canada who want to find EV charging stations locations to plug their Tesla Model S / Leaf / iMiEV / Volt / Focus EV / Plug-in Prius / Smart EV / BMW i3 / Kia Soul EV / etc.

Follow us on Twitter @EVChargeHub

-- What EV ChargeHub does --
EV & Tesla Charging Stations Map Interface:
-Find public electric vehicle charging stations
-Get driving directions to nearest EV or Tesla charging station
-Over 120 000 electric car charging station plugs (ev plugs) in the US & Canada
-See whats around while you recharge. Plugin your electric car & see what restaurants, hotels, parks, places are around your EV or Tesla charging station
-Get color coded live availability data from EV charging stations in the following networks: Chargepoint, Blink, Hydro Quebec's Circuit Electrique and AddEnergie Flo
-Found a new public charging station? Add it to the EV Charge Hub database
-Rate & add comments for all public electric vehicle supply equipment
-Use search feature to find Level 1, Level 2 (EV Plug) and DC Fast chargers (Tesla Superchargers, SAE DC Fast & CHAdeMO) anywhere across North America
-Smooth & responsive interface
-Filter and search EV charging stations to only display the ones you want (by network, by charging level, etc)
-Google Streetview to make it easier to see what's around an EV plug
-Directly call the network EVSE from the app to get more information (ex: Chargepoint, Tesla Supercharger, evGO, Blink, Electric Circuit, SemaCharge, VERnetwork)
-See traffic conditions directly on map & select map type
-Unique logos for Tesla Superchargers, SAE DC Fast chargers and CHAdeMO charging stations
-Share complete EV charging station info
-Detailed usage data for BC evCloud connected EV charging stations
-Request permission from other EV users for charger use ("plugshare-ing")
-In app charge session payment for selected networks

-- EV ChargeHub Features In Development --
-In app EV range estimation

Who should download EV Charge Hub:
-Electric car owners who want to find EV charging stations
-Prospective buyers of Tesla ModelS / Leaf / iMiEV / Volt / Focus EV / Plug-in Prius / Smart EV / Kia Soul EV / etc, who want to know where electric vehicle charging stations are before purchasing an electric car

title:
Chargehub EV & Tesla Charging
12.89.0

creator: Mogile Technologies
descriptionHtml:
⬇️ Download ChargeHub - the #1 app for EV drivers

👉 ChargeHub is the essential app for finding EV charging stations in the US and Canada for electric car drivers.

👉 ChargeHub provides seamless payment for EV charging sessions across compatible networks.

👉 ChargeHub boasts one of the largest EV driver communities in North America.

With ChargeHub you can:

✅ Access over 200,000 EV charging stations across the US and Canada.

✅ Pay for your EV charging sessions via the ChargeHub app at over 100,000 chargers across compatible networks.

✅ Search and find the nearest public electric car charger.

✅ View and share detailed site information on the EV charging map, for all EV charging stations, including photos, address, energy pricing, operating hours, number of chargers, connector types and payment methods.

✅ Check live availability of public electric vehicle charging stations compatible with your EV.

✅ View real-time EV charging statistics including power usage, energy costs, charging amperage, charge duration, and more!

✅ Refine your EV charging stations search with filters for network, charging level, connector type, power level, amenities in order to quickly find the chargers that meet your requirements.

✅ Filter EV chargers displayed on the map by desired connector types such as J1772 connectors, Tesla Superchargers, CHAdeMO, or SAE Combo DC Fast connectors.

✅ Find Level 1, Level 2, and DC Fast chargers (including Tesla Superchargers, SAE DC Fast, and CHAdeMO).

✅ Find free EV charging stations, free level 2 charging stations and free DC fast charging stations.

✅ Consult your EV charging history.

✅ Save your favourite and nearby EV charging stations for quick access.

✅ Plan your EV road trip with a built-in route planner that identifies charging stations along the way to charge your EV.

✅ View real-time traffic conditions and choose your preferred map view.

✅ Get notified about new EV charging stations installed nearby your preferred locations.

✅ Add pictures & new locations as you discover them.

✅ Rate and review public EV charging stations.

✅ Enjoy a simple and intuitive chat interface or call us for support when needed.

🛜 ChargeHub's map offers comprehensive information for most major EV charging networks across North America, including BC Hydro, ChargePoint, Circle K/Couche Tard, Blink, Shell Recharge, Hydro Quebec's Circuit Electrique, AddEnergie Flo, Ivy, Electrify America, Electrify Canada, Petro-Canada, ChargeLab, EVgo, Tesla, Co-op Connect, EcoCharge, EVGateway, EVCS, Evolve NY, EVoke, EVSmart, FPL Evolution, Hypercharge, Newfoundland, Semaconnect, Sun Country Highway, SWTCH, Volta, and more.
